<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-04-1297 </DOCNO><TEXT>Hydroelectric power plants have a very favourable public image: They produceneither waste gases nor waste water and utilize a natural, renewableenergy source. However, it is doubtful if this image is justified: ManyGerman rivers have been turned into rows of stale ponds by the necessarydams, and migrating fish are unable to pass imperfect fish passages orare cut to pieces by turbine blades.</TEXT></DOC>